SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYMonday 9 May S10 V3 Fresh from securing a place in the Uefa Europa League Conference final, Jose Mourinho’s Roma now chase a place in next season’s European club competition at the expense of Fiorentina tonight. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Antalyaspor vs Konyaspor: Konyaspor have gone 11 games without defeat against Antalyaspor but eight of those game have been drawn.M2 Hapoel Haifa vs Ashdod FC : Hapoel Haifa are unbeaten in their past six clashes with Ashdod, winning four of them.M3 Helsingborg vs Norrkoping: Norrkoping are 13-12 ahead in the win count of the past meetings between these two Swedish clubs with an additional 13 draws.M4 Varnamo vs Hacken: Varnamo have only one win from their opening six games of the new season in Sweden. Hacken’s last two away games both ended in 1-1 draws.M5 Elfsborg vs Djurgarden: Elfsborg had a 6-0 away win at Degerfors last Monday. Djurgarden scored four goals in their last game, at home to Sirius.M6 Fiorentina vs Roma: Roma have won five in a row over Fiorentina, including two away from home.M7 Derry City vs St Patrick’s Athletic: Derry have won the last three clashes with St Pats, including a 4-0 triumph away last month.M8 Shamrock Rovers vs Sligo Rovers: The two meetings already between these Irish clubs this season have both ended in draws.M9 Girona vs Tenerife: Both clubs are in the top six of the Spanish second division but not yet sure of places in the promotion playoffs. Tenerife have won once on nine past visits to Girona.M10 Belenenses vs Famalicao: Failure to win at home will likely condemn Belenenses to relegation. Famalicao have drawn twice and lost the other two of their past four matches. Suggested permutation:R4.00 3 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1,2 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1